        <abstract>
            <p>Wishes to use some of Fritz Müller’s observations in his paper on mimicry.</p> 
<p>CD’s reply and Huxley’s article ["Mr Darwin’s critics", <hi rend="italic">Contemp. Rev.</hi> 18 (1871): 443–76] have answered all of Mivart’s objections to natural selection as applied to man.</p> 
        </abstract>
